Choose from our sophisticated black or timeless white color options, both of which exude a chic and refined appeal. Thanks to its compact size, it fits seamlessly into any room without overpowering the decor.

【Suggest Two Person Setup】 We highly recommend Two-Person Installation for speed and ease. Before starting the installation, be sure to watch the installation video and read the user manual. This will help you understand the installation process and expedite the process better.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars One of the better stands I've bought
reviews.reviewText: They all take a little work to assemble, not a big deal. Just be sure to put the wood dowels all the way in before putting the top on.Great finish, no scratches or dents, it goes together very well and tightly. Everything is machined well, the holes are drilled correctly and all lines up perfect. The drawers all slide great, and the lines all match up uniformly when looking at the front. Worth the price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very impressed! I am a real person :)
reviews.reviewText: My husband and I built this together.First of all, we were EXTREMELY impressed with whoever designed this kit. It was incredibly well organized, easy to follow instructions, and most importantly contains EXTRA PARTS just in case! We kept commenting the whole time about the fact that the person who designed this kit is somewhere out in the world feeling good about themselves because they did a damn good job.A few tips/thoughts:-It was really nice and fun to build with someone if you can get a flow going. I think it took us less than an hour working together.-It was helpful to use a power drill, but REALLY important that you get the screws straight!-The thing is sturdy as can be due to both materials and design, and the drawers slide very smoothly (but again - it's up to you to make sure you screw the screws in straight!)Final assessment: This is a great value purchase. We highly recommend!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 6, 2024
reviews.reviewText: If you are wanting to do this without the use of a drill, good luck to ya! Tried that with just a screwdriver they supply you and I ended up causing my hand to bleed just a tiny bit. I would recommend using a drill. Between my grandpa and I, this took about 1 hour if not, a little less. The steps are easy to follow and it’s not too bad. This could be used for little things to help declutter your space but I wouldn’t expect to put really heavy items in these drawers. It’s a thin sheet of wood that seems breakable of you put too much weight on it. However, this could be used for makeup, toys, beauty products, snacks, anything really that doesn’t have too much weight. Aside from that, this product seems pretty good!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great drawer cabinet
reviews.reviewText: Yes there are a lot of parts and hardware, but the instructions are easy to follow and the assembled product is really nice. The black finish does show fingerprints, dust and smudges, but that's common for black furniture. The drawer glides are metal and they open and they close smoothly. The cabinet is basically fiberboard and cardboard, but it's quite sturdy and very nice quality for the price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Cheap, flimsy, drawers do not line up
reviews.reviewText: So these drawers looked great at first and I was pleasantly surprised by the clarity of instructions and how most of the pieces were solid wood. But there was one HUGE issue that ruined the whole thing. And that’s that the drawers do not line up!!! They say that you have to be super careful to lay the screws flat or else the drawers won’t close, and I did that. Literally even used a power drill to make sure of it. And yet the pieces still don’t line up on the inside so it’s virtually impossible to open and close the drawers. I have to slam them so hard each time. I’ve only had these drawers for a few days, but the inside pieces are already destroyed from my slamming. This whole things gonna crumble in another few days. Honestly, I’m shocked by this. How is it possible that the most important pieces of the entire furniture are misaligned??? It’s virtually unusable and it’s way too much effort to return. So I basically flushed $60 down the drain. Do yourself a favor and don’t buy this!!! Instead invest an extra $20 and get the ikea Alex drawers. I guess this is my karma for trying to be cheap…

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Liked these so much I bought 8 of them!
reviews.reviewText: I have a crazy amount of Lego. Looking online a lot of adult Lego fans were sorting their collections into either IKEA drawers or plastic drawers. I liked the IKEA look, but did not like the IKEA price. So I ordered two of these to see if I liked them. They are a tedious but easy build. It’s pretty hard to mess up this build, as it uses a limited selection of hardware to avoid any confusion with screw size, Etc. .The drawers move smoothly, although if the screws aren’t in 100% it may feel difficult to pull out. Don’t fret, just tighten the screws a bit more. I didn’t use the casters that were included, because I wanted to stack them(Not sure if they are supposed to be stacked but they seemed sturdy enough. However I will note, we did receive a caster with a broken brake tab.The build is surprisingly sturdy, even with the twist lock hardware. I would say the hardware included with this build is sturdier than real IKEA hardware. The locks actually feel strong and they let you know they are properly locked by clicking into place.Overall a great way to sort my collection and I love the nice clean look!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Cracking paint, particle board, long assembly
reviews.reviewText: This took 2-3 hours to assemble! The paint cracked easily, the quality was cheap, and amny parts were dinged up. I wouldn't say the drawers are super smooth like a dresser's would be, but that might be just how I put the screws on. Even so, this cabinet should be 20$ max. It's just poor quality stuff. You're better off buying something that's real wood, maybe vintage. Be prepared to put time into assembling this.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 20, 2024
reviews.reviewText: There are a lot of parts, but it’s repetitive and not difficult to figure out. Just line up all the parts based on the labeling and methodically proceed with assembly. Using a drill to put in all the screws makes it go quickly. I’m very pleased with the quality. I didn’t use the casters on the bottom due to space. It fits beautifully beneath the counter in an empty space in the bathroom.
